    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-05-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="595"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                <head>595. Telegram 6 from Geneva to Warsaw<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d595fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/5–556.
                        Confidential; Limit Distribution. Repeated to the Department of State as
                        telegram 1849.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-05-05"
                            >May 5, 1956, 4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d595-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d595-1"/>
                <p>1849. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> asked for postponement our May 5
                    meeting to May 11. Do you know of any development that would require his
                    presence in Warsaw during that period? He traveled to Warsaw April 27 presumably
                    attend May 1 celebration but I have not (repeat not) been able to determine
                    whether or when he returned Geneva.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
